caption: Used to be great.  Things have slipped since the quarantine.
Really appreciated outdoor seating during 2020 & love their cobb salad. I order it every time we visit. Priced right & always fresh.
Cute place. Staff was very friendly and helpful
Fantastic food! Shrimp Tacos and The Sophie Roll will not disappoint, excellent service. Top Tier local joint!!
Staff is all amazing and they have one of the best bourbon selections in town.
Love the atmosphere, service, cocktails and food!!! One of my favorite local restaurants!!! Will always recommend!!!
Great food and amazing bourbon.  Can't wait to go back.
Great place for food, drinks, and ambiance!
Came here for lunch. Pretty awful overall
Outstanding food and service
Best burger I ever had!!
Good drinks!
Great  Food. Friendly service. Tell Inch I said Hi.
Loved the woodford burger!
Lunch was delicious!!!

Just ordered 2 burgers from here, I have had better at Steak n Shake. 😩 😭 The burgers are crazy crazy dry. It is not worth the amount paid for. The fries are really yummy and crunchy though..  So theres that.
Great food and people. A favorite place.

I politely asked the waitress how their shrimp scampi was and instead of the usual “great” or “I hear its great” received an attitude on how she didn’t eat meat so she didn’t know. So I asked if shrimp was meat and she informed me, again with an edge in her voice, that she doesn’t eat anything with a heartbeat. So I ordered it anyway. The meal arrives and it is 5 shrimp on a bed of rice, not linguini. I will say it was excellent, but it was not a pleasant dining experience. I’m eating outside due to COVID and supporting a long-time local business, and I get a waitress who clearly had no tolerance for anything and a meal that was not what I ordered. I actually felt belittled. But at least now I know shrimp is considered meat.

Reality bites is an amazing place to go to if you're looking for a fun place to go with friends. Great staff, knowledgable bartender and amazing food. I also have really enjoyed getting food delivered to my job for lunch. Everytime I receive an order delivered to work there has been a personal note thanking me for ordering. The chef definitely shows that he cares and appreciates his customers and what entrees he creates. Anytime anyone asks for somewhere to go I always recommend coming here.
Fantastic food, great staff and atmosphere. I am never disappointed!

Reality Bites is the place to go for a memorable night out. My boyfriend and I experienced incredible service from the moment we walked in. It was also obvious that everyone else who was dining was enjoying their time and that the staff was paying attention to details. The food was delicious and is plated beautifully! It makes for an extra special evening when the head chef himself visits the guests whilst dining and puts a face to the great meal. I'm not one to try new food each time I visit the same restaurant, but I just don't want to miss a single dish at Reality Bites. Can't wait to be back!!!
The best sushi in town!!  Delicious food, great prices, and service was fantastic.  Big time compliments to the chef.
Great food great friendly  staff favorites  go-to downtown  spot before drinks

This is an awesome place!! Great atmosphere and such a fun outgoing staff. It’s a nice place to go if you’re looking for a date night or if you want to meet up with friends. I love their food, their potstickers are to die for! Check it out, you won’t regret it!
Really good menu.
A Downtown Bloomington jewel.

Reality bites does bite!  Showed up at 7:10 for a 7:15 reservation and weren’t seated until 7:30. Service was incredibly slow and we didn’t not receive our food until 8:45.  Our friends never even receive the appetizer they ordered.  We had to ask to be compensated for the wait and they were not going to give it to us until we asked for a manager.  We will not be going back. I would not recommend.  Would give zero stars if it were an option.
Went there for the first time and the food was really good and well prices ! Service was awesome! Would definitely recommend and will return!
Great food, great service !
Amazing as always.
Excellent food & great atmosphere!
Friendly service tasty unique food.
Food and service was great!  8 - 10 craft beers on tap.
Good food.

Late lunch. Delicious salad, pork taco and Pinot Grigio. Sweet waitress. Pleasant atmosphere. Good music that was too loud for our conversation and they happily lowered the volume. Would go again in a minute.
Food was fabulous but they brought each of us the wrong food first time around. Loved the cozy atmosphere.
The food is so good! The head chef came out and asked how we liked the food! I loved that brandon came out and was proud of his food! I would come back again!!! He puts his heart into his food!!
Good food. Good service. Nice people.
Fantastic! Kyle was great on Wednesday date night! Food was fabulous! Inch runs a fantastic restaurant experience!
Food sucked very expensive. Won't be going back.
The food was excellent. New menu options,  and remodeled section was nicely done. Props to whoever the head cook is!

The spinach artichoke dip was delicious! We also had the taco egg roll feature, which was crispy and garnished well. I had the impossibility burger and it was ok, a little thin and overcooked. They also have $5 margaritas on Tuesdays. They were fair sized but a little syrupy for my liking. Overall, good visit with nice ambiance.
Great flavors, nice unique options.  Large portion of Carne Asada nachos.  Good drinks.
Great food and menu options
Ordered the spicy shrimp and falafel balls. Shrimp was not really spicy but tasty. Falafel were dry, crumbly and needed salt.  Bonnie was very friendly and the atmosphere is good.
Inch...please fix the horrible sewer smell!
Not as good as I remember - slightly overpriced for what you get + two dishes were quite overdone. Will try again and order differently to compare.

Went with a large group and the waitress impressively handled our multiple drink orders and indecisiveness. It is a bit dark in here, the sound level is low. I had a burger which was good. The menu has a decent variety- a few people in our group got tacos which they all raved about. The beer selection leaves a lot to be desired, but I do think they are known for specialty drinks so it is what it is.
Good food and interesting menu items that you can't find everywhere. Wasn't busy on a Friday for lunch so it was fast. Service was friendly.

Alright. Here we go. Before coming to this place I had passed it multiple times. I always looked forward to one day actually going, well yesterday was that day. I was excited to try it out. Let's start with service. Our original waitress was new, so she didn't know anything about anything on the menu. I understand being new can be difficult, but when you don't even know what the restaurant you're working for is serving you are no help to anyone, carry a cheat sheet or something. Memorize it. Idk. Anyways the food. The food was meh. We started with the goat cheese balls and the bang bang shrimp. The goat cheese balls were good, but they weren't quite there. The balls were huge. The ratio of breading to cheese was not ideal. Smaller balls would be ideal. Lol As for the shrimp, it was weak I could literally go to Kroger, get frozen shrimp, throw it in the oven and dip it in spicy mustard and it would be the exact same thing I received at this place. I also tried the bacon wrapped dates which were far too wet and far too burnt. I then tried the smashed chickpea sandwich, while it was okay, again it just fell short. Not a lot of flavor. For desert we got cake bites and brown butter cake which was really good. I have zero complaints about the desert. Ya'll can absolutely improve and I will probably eat there again in the future and give it another try. 👍🔮

Made a reservation at this location for a Saturday night and was seated promptly. We ordered very much tapas style getting a special app (bang bang shrimp) as well as the goat cheese balls. Then we split the smashed chickpea sandwich with fries and finished with the cake bites and the brown butter cake.  All and all the food was 50/50 hit or miss. The shrimp was decent & the cheese balls were okay. The sandwich was pretty good and so were the fries. The cake balls were okay: lemon was solid but the red velvet was bad, honestly. The butter cake was awesome. Overall, the menu made it sound like we were going to get something spectacular but then it came out looking kind of thrown together.  If everything was 2 to 4 dollars cheaper I'd be all in on this place. But I spent $50 for a meal I could make myself.  Beyond the food, the decor was beautiful but the service was subpar because our waitress was new and hadn't really memorized the menu at all. The whole process took longer than I'd have liked. I might go back again, but not likely when I can go somewhere else with similar prices.
Good, but overpriced.

Waiter quit mid-meal - never had that happen to me before. He was good but there were more issues than a typical restaurant visit. Pork belly looked like pulled chicken. Took at least five minutes between first and last meal brought out.
Creative menu with a lot of variety, good place to gather with friends and try new things.  Not inexpensive, but quality.
Burger was over cooked
Great friendly service and great food! Nice hidden gem in downtown Bloomington.
Delicious and fun!!
The owner came up to me and said that I looked 12 years old. I am a almost college graduate who was not looking to be insulted. Extremely disappointed and will not be going back.

Been wanting to visit this place for some time and was finally able to check it out. Staff was extremely friendly and I came on a night that wasn’t super busy. Ordered the Asian spring rolls to start-was surprised they were fried but tasty. Then ordered the month’s specialty sunset tacos and the shrimp risotto. Risotto was delicious but wish there was more shrimp and for the tacos there was barely anything in them. It was more tortilla than anything. Disappointed especially with how pricey the items are. Would expect a bit more food for the price as well as a better presentation. For dessert, I ordered the blueberry crumble which was good. Overall not super impressed with the amount of food for the price.
One of my favorites! Always great food, great people and very good vibe! Butch, Inchol and rest of the staff are awesome!
Excellent food. Highly recommend the risotto. Clean. Not a lot of seating.
Try all the specials
Always wonderful food.
Nice upscale restaurant with good food!
Food was good but pricey for the portion size
Great vibe and ever changing menu. Always good.
Very nice place for a date. Great food. Nice people.
Delicious
Bonnie is a funny bartender. Good food
Great for and cocktails.  They make a really good old fashion.
In Down from Arizona And what a really cool place to eat And have some tasty adult beverages
Very one note in flavor. To expensive

Visited the on 10/30, so it was as slow and the kitchen closed early. Regardless itwas a great experience. The bartender, Josh, was very nice and made us feel like regulars. Drinks were amazing. Will be back to try the food!
Only bar in downtown bloom to get a cocktail
Dinner, drinks, service, restaurant ambiance...all great here!
Excellent tapas restaurant! A bit pricey I usually spend over $50 for two people so prepare the wallet. Drinks are good too!
Food was fresh and really delicious, affordable lunch prices as well. The music is not your typical radio station so it made for a lovely sounding enviroment. Kyle was amazing
Truly a staff that values their community, donated dinner for a public event and exceeded our expectations in quality & service.

Reality Bites catered a small community event for us and went completely above and beyond our expectations! The food was delicious and the presentation was absolutely delightful! A huge thank you to Heaven for making this happen!!

My favorite place to eat in Bloomington. It's all small shareable plates which is great for friends or a girls night out. My favorite things on the menu are the pork tacos and goat cheese balls with berry sauce. They also have a great drink selection.
Great food, great service. Bartenders know what they are doing and the staff is polite and professional.
Beautiful restaurant with lots of unique delicious appetizers. I have not tried the entrees yet but they looked great too. I really enjoyed the atmosphere and great service.
Small place with small plates, food and drinks are good though. Wide variety of alcohol as well.

This was an excellent late dinner stop on an impromptu road trip. The kitchen is open until 11:00. The food was very good, and the service was excellent despite it being late. There was a decent selection of local craft beer and regional beer. I'll be back.
My rating reflects the quality of food. It was fantastic. The noise level was so loud, I couldn't wait to get out. I will never go back.
Friendly service, decent food.
Delicious food, great drinks, wonderful desserts. Staff is friendly. What more could one ask for?
Another good dinner
Great food deserts are amazing.. little expensive though.
Great place great food. Our waiter Delton was fabulous.
Expensive, but good

New owner is a scumbag. Had lots of friends work here in the past and really enjoyed the food the original owner kept on the menu with the help of his chef. Chef and business owner changed and I'd never return.
Really good place for a date. Hidden gem in bloomington. Even though i wasnt a huge fan of the goat cheese balls, i enjoyed my craft beer and my steak was glorious. Would reccomend.
Amazing food

The staff was welcoming and professional.  They also had really good food.  Me and a friend had fried goat cheese balls and fish tacos.  The place was small, but there is also a more private meeting space for parties.
excellent tapas and drinks
Great food, atmosphere and waiter!!
Great Tapas/sharable items and entrees. Tapas can be an entree also.
Had an incredible experience having dinner! Food was top notch and the atmosphere was classy and perfect to bring a date. Will be going back again!

I went on New Year's Eve, my second time here with a large group of friends. The staff is very friendly and the atmosphere manages to mix class and trend together very well. There is a pleasant variety of drink selections and the menu choices are well rounded. Dinner tasted magnificent and was presented beautifully. This spot is one of Bloomington's treasures.
Cozy places with small plates and entrees. The food was decent but my dish came out cold and took an hour to arrive.
Always great!
We love this place! Butch and his staff are phenomenal. The food and beverage choices never disappoint. The atmosphere makes us feel like we're somehow, not in BloNo anymore.
Love this place!   Wish Dalton was a full time bartender!  Love the fish taco special on Tuesdays!
Great place for a night out downtown!
Menu changes frequently, atmosphere can be loud sometimes.  Small outdoor seating area when weather is nice.
Good food but a little pricey for a quick lunch.
Great environment, food with a friendly staff! Highly recommended!
Awesome menu.  Great fish tacos
Dinner for two.  Good food, good service, good company.  And yes, the wine was a great pairing.
I have been here three times, and the food and service is always excellent!
Great food.
I like the quick bites here, chicken taco and cocktails are really good
Second time here, pork tacos did not disappoint.
After trying several things from the menu I am convinced this place thrives on hype and atmosphere. The food just wasn't good.
Great food but pricey. Owners/management are rude however.
Clean hall. Perfect for smaller gatherings
Great food, and service. Lovely dinner!
Very nice low lit atmosphere. Great for dates. Food is superb.

Food is ok. I had heard really good things about it, so my wife and I went for dinner. We were both pretty disappointed. Nothing was bad, but we didn't think anything was great. I probably won't go back.

There was a very large chunk of crusted cheese on my plate when we sat down.  I told the lady behind the bar and she didn't apologize, just said that the table hadn't been bussed, but there was new silverware on it and she's the one that had told us to sit down.  I asked politely for a new plate.   The waitress comes back with the SAME dirty plate.  When I told her, she didn't give an apology or anything, just took it and went back inside...we thought it was really gross so we told them we were going to eat elsewhere and they didn't care.  "okay bye" is all they said...seriously? The atmosphere was also dark and uninviting.  I've eaten here a few other times and it was generally okay, but they clearly don't care about their customers or have the decency to admit when they are wrong.  Never going there again.
Great food. Great intimate atmosphere.

Nice spot with good food and drinks.  Had a couple of disappointing experiences here which prevent me coming back often.  Once, it seemed like half of the menu was unavailable while another time the waitress forgot about our table.
Food, staff, ambiance all top notch. This place is the only other bar worth seeing in the area.
Great place for a date night. Great food, classy bartenders, drinks are always good here. I'm definitely a fan
Unique and delicious food items. Great atmosphere!
Good food good wifi
My wife and I don't have many free nights out alone so when we do we usually go here. Always good food. Always interesting food. Not easy on the pockets but it is worth it.
Great beer, great Risotto Cakes!

Absolutely amazing tapas restaurant in downtown Bloomington. The drinks alone are worth stopping in for. They have martinis and cocktails and a huge wine list. The food is unique and fresh. They have hot plates, cold plates, really something for everyone. The atmosphere is great - dark with a warm wood bar and brick wall. It's the type of place that can be fancy or casual. They even do events like whiskey or wine tastings. Check the calendar. I highly recommend this restaurant.
The go-to place for dinner when we have friends from out of town!
Excellent food!

Hands down my favorite place to eat in town.  Great bar. Amazing food.  Love the atmosphere. Great place for a date or dinner out with friends.  Bacon wrapped dates are a must. Have yet to find something on the menu I don't love.

Good atmosphere. Outside seating. Good food. It's a nice place to go for good food or a drink with a friend. Good date spot as well. They have a bunch of small plate shareable appetizers but also have some really good entrees.
Best restaurant in town! Great food, drinks, and service!!!
Quaint atmosphere.  Delicious food.  Definitely a visit again place.  Wonderful, friendly staff
Very delicious. Maybe my dislike of onions is what downgraded my otherwise five star review... Nice setting, great selection, professional staff and of course, good people.

I had never been here before, but decided to take the risk and make reservations for me and 8 other people for my college graduation. I couldn't have been more pleased with my experience. This is some of the best food I have ever had and the restaurant was clean, quite, and had a good atmosphere. I couldn't believe this awesome place was just down the street from places like Fat Jacks, Drifter's, and Mulligans.  I got the Mahi-Mahi, which had crab meat and panko bread crumbs on top, next to mashed potatoes (to die for) and some of the best asparagus I've ever had. The staff is extremely knowledgeable-half my relatives have a gluten intolerance and they knew exactly what couldn't be on certain items and what could. This restaurant also has gluten free menus, which can sometimes be hard to find.  All in all I would DEFINITELY RECOMMEND this place!
Great atmospthere. The food was good- we had some "warm" and "cold" bites. I thought everything was a little overprices. The entrees looked great, though. The service was excellent.
Pretty good food, but a bit overpriced for what you get (quality-wise that is). Be warned that it has a sports bar atmosphere and can get quite loud.
I got the pork tacos and they were delicious!  My wife got the breaded scallops and was very happy with them.  We will be going back!!

We did appetizers.  Goat cheese balls, chicken Skewers and fried calamari.  The food was great, the goat cheese balls were extremely memorable, they know how to use the right amount of spice, the portions were perfectly sized, every plate that went past us to another table looked and smelled amazing and the staff was friendly but not overbearing.  I would highly recommend this to any food enthusiast!
Good food, but it's overpriced. Why? I think it's a place for hipsters who will pay the price to look cool. But the food was good and clean.

I'm really sad that this place is currently closed because it is getting revamped. It recently got bought by new management. I hope they don't change too much about it. It was one of the few bars in the area that isn't full of frat boys or rednecks.

I loved the bruschetta chicken.  And the pork tacos are also delicious.  I would not compare it to Olive Garden or Red Lobster.  Although if you are dumb enough to order seafood in Illinois you might as well go to Long John Silvers.  I had great service and the owner even came by my table to check on us.  The place was packed so we waited 20 minutes at the bar.  I will definitely be going back. I'm always looking for a restaurant that is not a chain and finally found one worth going to.
